WEBVTT

00:00.860 --> 00:02.236
- HELP WANTED, HUH?

00:03.760 --> 00:05.091
- I NEED SOMEONE
WITH PHOTOGRAPHY EXPERIENCE.

00:05.210 --> 00:06.165
- [screams]
OH, MY GOD!

00:06.280 --> 00:07.542
- IT'S BEEN FIVE MONTHS.

00:07.660 --> 00:09.799
WE CAN'T KEEP WALKING
ON EGGSHELLS

00:09.900 --> 00:11.037
AROUND THIS BOY.

00:11.140 --> 00:12.072
- I FEEL LIKE I'M WAITING

00:12.180 --> 00:13.488
TO FALL IN LOVE WITH OUR SON.

00:13.590 --> 00:16.047
- TODAY'S THE BIG DAY, HUH?
AMY COMES BACK FROM CAMP.

00:16.150 --> 00:17.378
- SHE SEEMS KIND OF DISTANT
OR SOMETHING.

00:17.500 --> 00:19.047
OH, MY GOD,
I MISSED YOU SO MUCH.

00:19.150 --> 00:21.971
- I MISSED YOU TOO.

00:22.090 --> 00:23.159
- I JUST HAVE TO TELL YOU

00:23.260 --> 00:24.534
THAT I GOT INTO CORNELL
EARLY ADMISSION.

00:24.640 --> 00:26.699
- I'M GONNA MISS YOU.

00:33.480 --> 00:33.957
[giggling]

00:34.060 --> 00:37.188
[low moaning]

00:43.690 --> 00:45.066
- OHH.

00:45.180 --> 00:47.102
I LOVE OUR SON, BUT I LOVE
WHEN HE'S AT GRANDMA'S.

00:47.210 --> 00:49.792
- YEAH.
[laughter]

00:49.910 --> 00:51.423
YEAH.

00:51.530 --> 00:53.760
- YOU KNOW, NEXT TIME
LET'S DO IT IN THE LAUNDRY ROOM.

00:53.880 --> 00:54.767
- MM.
- WE'LL GET EVERY ROOM

00:54.880 --> 00:56.939
IN THE HOUSE.
- [glggleSJ

00:57.050 --> 00:57.869
[cell phone chimes]

00:57.980 --> 00:59.083
- UH-OH.
THAT COULD BE HER.

00:59.190 --> 01:01.750
COULD BE YOUR MAMA.

01:01.850 --> 01:03.124
- DON'T ANSWER IT.

01:03.230 --> 01:06.506
- OH.
NO, IT'S ADAM.

01:06.610 --> 01:08.714
"REMIND AMBER
TO PICK UP TONER TOMORROW"?

01:08.820 --> 01:10.094
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

01:10.200 --> 01:12.339
THESE ARE THE TEXTS HE'S SENDING
AT 10:00 P.M.?

01:12.450 --> 01:14.441
WE ARE OFFICIALLY
THE HOTTEST BRAVERMAN COUPLE.

01:14.550 --> 01:16.199
- YOU KNOW,
THIS REALLY DRIVES ME NUTS.

01:16.310 --> 01:17.823
IT TAKES CROSBY FOREVER
TO RESPOND

01:17.930 --> 01:19.249
TO AN EMAIL
OR A TEXT.

01:19.350 --> 01:21.625
HOW HARD COULD IT BE
JUST TO SAY, "OKAY, I GOT IT"?

01:21.730 --> 01:22.958
- MAYBE HE'S BUSY, HONEY.

01:23.080 --> 01:25.696
- HONEY, IT'S SUNDAY NIGHT.

01:25.800 --> 01:28.940
- OHH.

01:29.050 --> 01:30.085
- WHAT?
WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING AT?

01:30.190 --> 01:31.259
- NOTHING.
- HONEY, WHAT ARE YOU--

01:31.360 --> 01:33.043
- IT'S NOTHING.
WHAT?

01:33.160 --> 01:34.252
- WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING
AT PUPPIES FOR?

01:34.370 --> 01:35.394
- WE ALWAYS TALKED
ABOUT GETTING A DOG.

01:35.500 --> 01:36.501
- NO.
NO, WE DIDN'T.

01:36.610 --> 01:38.498
- YES, WE DID.
- NO, WE HAVEN'T.

01:38.610 --> 01:39.645
- ADAM.

01:39.750 --> 01:41.638
LISTEN, WE HAVE.
LOOK AT HOW CUTE THIS GUY--

01:41.750 --> 01:42.853
- OH, COME ON, HONEY,
I KNOW THAT YOU MISS HADDIE,

01:42.960 --> 01:43.995
BUT REALLY?

01:44.100 --> 01:45.260
- THIS DOG DOES NOT LOOK
LIKE HADDIE.

01:45.380 --> 01:47.200
- HADDIE--THAT DOG LOOKS EXACTLY
LIKE HADDIE.

01:47.310 --> 01:48.686
- THIS ONE?
- YES.

01:48.790 --> 01:51.031
- NO, IT DOESN'T.
OKAY, MAYBE A LITTLE BIT.

01:51.140 --> 01:52.653
THE CURLS
ARE A LITTLE DIFFERENT.

01:52.760 --> 01:53.931
- MM-HMM.
- THE EYES ARE NOT THE SAME.

01:54.040 --> 01:56.588
- WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?
- NOTHING.

01:56.700 --> 01:59.077
NOTHING. I'M JUST LOOKING.
- OKAY.

01:59.180 --> 02:00.932
- I'M NOT SAYING WE'RE GOING
TO GET A DOG.

02:01.050 --> 02:02.119
WE'RE TALKING ABOUT A DOG.

02:02.220 --> 02:03.448
- WE'RE TALKING
ABOUT GETTING A DOG?

02:03.570 --> 02:05.140
- MM-HMM.
- HONEY, I LOVE DOGS,

02:05.260 --> 02:06.568
BUT I ALSO KNOW
WHAT A ROYAL PAIN IN THE ASS

02:06.670 --> 02:08.558
HAVING A PUPPY CAN BE.
- THEY'RE CUTE. THEY'RE CUDDLY.

02:08.680 --> 02:10.295
- THAT GUY IS GOING
TO DESTROY MY HOUSE.

02:10.400 --> 02:11.219
HE'S GONNA CRAP
ALL OVER THE PLACE.

02:11.330 --> 02:12.888
- SO WHAT?
SO DO YOU.

02:12.990 --> 02:15.538
[giggIeSJ

02:15.650 --> 02:17.231
I'M JUST KIDDING.
- THEY'RE CUTE, HONEY,

02:17.340 --> 02:18.125
BUT IT'S A BIG--
IT'S A BIG COMMITMENT.

02:18.240 --> 02:19.571
- THEY ARE CUTE.
RESEARCH SHOWS

02:19.690 --> 02:20.236
THAT THIS DOG
WOULD BE GOOD FOR MAX

02:20.340 --> 02:22.308
AS A COMPANION.

02:22.410 --> 02:23.513
THEY'RE COMPATIBLE FOR KIDS

02:23.620 --> 02:25.064
ON THE AUTISM SPECTRUM,
THEY ARE.

02:25.170 --> 02:26.580
- MM-HMM.
ALL RIGHT.

02:26.690 --> 02:28.134
WELL, LET'S JUST MAKE SURE
WE TAKE A BEAT

02:28.250 --> 02:29.512
BEFORE WE JUST RUN OFF
AND GET A DOG.

02:29.630 --> 02:32.451
LET'S MAKE SURE WE'RE THINKING
RATIONALLY ABOUT THIS.

02:32.560 --> 02:33.356
- AND THERE'S ANOTHER ONE
I WANT TO SHOW YOU TOO.

02:33.460 --> 02:34.836
- IT'S A 14-YEAR COMMITMENT.

02:34.940 --> 02:38.114
- THIS ONE LOOKS
LIKE YOUR MOM.

02:38.220 --> 02:40.848
RUFF.
- WE'LL THINK ABOUT IT.

02:40.950 --> 02:44.056
- SMILE
AND SAY, "SENIOR."

02:44.160 --> 02:46.219
"SENIOR." OH, WAIT.
HOLD ON, I'M ON VIDEO.

02:46.330 --> 02:47.536
CRUD. ONE MORE TIME,
ONE MORE TIME.

02:47.650 --> 02:48.742
- I REALLY HAVE TO PICK HER UP
AT 7:45, SO...

02:48.850 --> 02:50.169
- I KNOW, I KNOW, I KNOW.
- WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

02:50.270 --> 02:50.952
WE GOT TO GET THIS.
- IT WON'T STOP RECORDING.

02:51.060 --> 02:51.924
OKAY, SMILE.

02:52.030 --> 02:53.884
- GOOD. YEAH.
- YAY!

02:54.000 --> 02:55.194
- GREAT.
I'M GLAD WE GOT THAT.

02:55.310 --> 02:57.449
- HEY, GRANDSON, WAIT A MINUTE,
WAIT A MINUTE.

02:57.550 --> 02:58.778
I WANT TO TELL YOU SOMETHING.
- MM-HMM.

02:58.900 --> 03:01.619
- NOW, FOR THE NEXT 12 MONTHS,
I WANT YOU TO BEHOLD

03:01.730 --> 03:05.860
THE BREAST OF KNOWLEDGE,
THRUST YOURSELF UPON IT,

03:05.970 --> 03:07.039
AND SUCK.
- GROSS, DAD.

03:07.150 --> 03:08.310
WHY DOES KNOWLEDGE
HAVE BOOBS?

03:08.420 --> 03:10.593
UH, LISTEN, HONEY, PICK ME UP
AT 5:00, OKAY?

03:10.700 --> 03:12.008
DON'T FORGET.
- YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

03:12.120 --> 03:13.018
- AND, LISTEN, IF YOU USE
THE BLINKER

03:13.120 --> 03:14.212
AND THE WINDSHIELD WIPERS

03:14.330 --> 03:15.467
AT THE SAME TIME,
THE CAR WILL SHAKE, SO...

03:15.570 --> 03:17.049
- OH, JEEZ.
- IT'S ACTUALLY NOT RAINING.

03:17.160 --> 03:18.252
BUT--
- WELL, YOU NEVER KNOW.

03:18.370 --> 03:19.359
HONEY, HAVE A GREAT FIRST DAY.
- ALL RIGHT.

03:19.470 --> 03:20.630
- YUP.
- SAY HI TO AMY.

03:20.750 --> 03:23.082
- BYE, GUYS. I WILL.
- BE POLITE TO EVERYBODY.

03:23.200 --> 03:25.225
- BYE, GUYS.
- DON'T FORGET TO...

03:25.340 --> 03:27.228
WASH YOUR HANDS.
- BYE.

03:27.340 --> 03:30.207
SEE YOU LATER, GRAN--
"WASH YOUR HANDS"?

03:30.310 --> 03:30.924
- I DON'T KNOW.

03:31.030 --> 03:33.749
[sighs]

03:33.860 --> 03:36.067
- ONE ANCHOW-PEANUT BUTTER
SANDWICH.

03:36.180 --> 03:37.863
THAT'S YOUR FAVORITE, RIGHT?
- NO.

03:37.970 --> 03:38.413
THANK YOU.
- HEY, VICTOR.

03:38.520 --> 03:41.080
COME GET YOUR LUNCH.

03:41.180 --> 03:42.693
OH, YEAH, DON'T FORGET
YOUR SUGAR WATER.

03:42.800 --> 03:43.971
- ORANGE.
- VICTOR?

03:44.080 --> 03:45.934
BUDDY, WE DON'T WANT YOU
TO BE LATE ON YOUR FIRST DAY

03:46.050 --> 03:46.835
OF SCHOOL.

03:46.950 --> 03:48.110
HI.

03:48.220 --> 03:50.256
- I DON'T FEEL GOOD.

03:50.360 --> 03:52.225
- WHAT'S THE MATTER?

03:52.330 --> 03:53.080
- MY HEAD HURTS,
AND SO DOES MY STOMACH.

03:53.190 --> 03:56.079
- OH, BOY.

03:56.200 --> 03:57.770
LET'S SEE.

03:57.890 --> 03:59.198
OKAY, WELL,
YOU DON'T FEEL TOO WARM.

03:59.300 --> 04:00.881
- IT'S MOSTLY MY STOMACH.

04:00.990 --> 04:03.094
- HEY.

04:03.200 --> 04:04.474
GUYS, IT'S TEN TILL.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

04:04.580 --> 04:05.786
- VICTOR DOESN'T FEEL WELL.

04:05.900 --> 04:08.619
I THINK THAT WE'RE GONNA HAVE
TO KEEP YOU HOME.

04:08.730 --> 04:10.823
- BUT, HON,
IT'S THE FIRST DAY.

04:10.940 --> 04:13.101
- I KNOW,
BUT WHAT IF HE'S CONTAGIOUS?

04:13.210 --> 04:14.620
AND, YOU KNOW,
WE CAN'T DO THAT.

04:14.730 --> 04:16.618
- CAN YOU STAY,
AND I'LL TAKE SYD?

04:16.730 --> 04:17.628
- YEAH, YEAH.

04:17.740 --> 04:19.833
- AND I WILL CALL YOU
IN AN HOUR.

04:19.940 --> 04:23.489
OKAY, BUDDY?
I DO NOT LIKE YOU BEING SICK.

04:23.600 --> 04:24.703
ALL RIGHT.
- ALL RIGHT.

04:24.810 --> 04:27.984
- BYE, DADDY.
BYE, VICTOR. FEEL BETTER.

04:28.090 --> 04:28.943
- BYE.
- BYE. HAVE A GOOD DAY.

04:29.060 --> 04:30.607
- YOU TOO.
- LOVE YOU, DADDY.

04:30.710 --> 04:33.224
- BYE, LADIES.

04:33.340 --> 04:34.819
ALL RIGHT, MAN.

04:34.920 --> 04:37.787
WELL, LET'S HEAD UPSTAIRS
AND GET YOU INTO BED.

04:37.890 --> 04:40.711
- CAN I LAY ON THE COUCH?
THERE'S A TV THERE.

04:40.830 --> 04:44.345
- OKAY.
- AND THAT BRINGS US TO FRIDAY.

04:44.450 --> 04:47.658
DRT.
WHAT IS DRT?

04:47.770 --> 04:48.998
- OH, IT'S--
- DAVE RAY TRIO.

04:49.110 --> 04:50.623
- YES.
- JAZZ AND STUFF.

04:50.730 --> 04:51.697
- AND THEY ARE SCHEDULED
FOR HALF A DAY ONLY.

04:51.800 --> 04:53.620
WHY?
- BECAUSE THEY COULDN'T AFFORD

04:53.740 --> 04:54.809
A WHOLE DAY.
[cell phone chiming]

04:54.910 --> 04:56.832
- WELL, WE HAVE A HALF DAY
THAT'S UNBOOKED.

04:56.950 --> 04:58.326
WHAT ARE WE GONNA--
- I DON'T KNOW.

04:58.430 --> 04:59.419
DO YOU WANT ME TO SEE

04:59.540 --> 05:00.939
IF I CAN MOVE LANDON'S SESSION
TO THEN?

05:01.050 --> 05:02.460
- I'M SORRY. HOLD ON.
THAT IS A GREAT IDEA.

05:02.570 --> 05:03.502
YES, THANK YOU.
- I'M GONNA GET SOME COFFEE.

05:03.610 --> 05:06.010
- WHAT IS
THAT INCESSANT BEEPING

05:06.130 --> 05:07.267
THAT IT'S DOING?

05:07.370 --> 05:08.951
- IT'S JUST A CALENDAR APP
THAT I HAVE.

05:09.060 --> 05:11.642
KRISTINA LETS ME KNOW IF SHE
ADDS SOMETHING TO OUR SCHEDULE.

05:11.750 --> 05:14.207
- WELL, IT'S REAL ANNOYING.
IT'S GOING OFF ALL THE TIME.

05:14.310 --> 05:15.447
- YEAH, JUST LIKE A GUY WHO
PLAYS A GUITAR DURING A MEETING.

05:15.550 --> 05:16.687
I HAPPEN TO LIKE THIS APP,
OKAY?

05:16.790 --> 05:18.792
WE HAVE BUSY LIVES.
IT KEEPS US IN SYNC.

05:18.900 --> 05:20.481
- LET'S SEE WHAT SHE JUST ADDED.
- GIVE ME THAT BACK.

05:20.590 --> 05:22.763
- CAN WE? OH, SHE HAS
A HAIR APPOINTMENT AT 1:00.

05:22.870 --> 05:23.837
THANK GOD THAT CAME THROUGH.
- IT'S GOOD FOR ME TO KNOW THAT.

05:23.940 --> 05:25.828
- "WE HAVE DINNER AT 6:00."
- YUP.

05:25.940 --> 05:27.168
- MAYBE FORGOT TO EAT
IF THAT WASN'T THERE.

05:27.290 --> 05:28.598
- CAN WE GET BACK
TO THE SCHEDULE, PLEASE?

05:28.700 --> 05:30.565
- TRIP TO THE GYNECOLOGIST?
- DO YOU MIND?

05:30.670 --> 05:32.831
THAT'S PRIVATE INFORMATION.
- 10:00 PM. TO QUESTION MARK--

05:32.950 --> 05:34.736
FUNKYTOWN.

05:34.850 --> 05:36.158
- WHAT?

05:36.260 --> 05:37.329
- WHAT IS FUNKYTOWN?

05:37.440 --> 05:38.748
- IT'S NOTHING.
GIVE ME THE PHONE.

05:38.850 --> 05:40.158
- IT'S OPEN-ENDED. IT GOES FROM
10:00 TO GOD KNOWS WHEN.

05:40.270 --> 05:42.295
- I DON'T KNOW
WHAT IT IS.

05:42.410 --> 05:44.196
- YOU'RE CALLING SEX
"FUNKYTOWN."

05:44.300 --> 05:45.267
- NO, WE ARE NOT.
NO, WE DO NOT.

05:45.370 --> 05:47.338
- YES, YOU ARE.

05:47.450 --> 05:48.474
- THEN WHAT IS FUNKYTOWN?
- ALL RIGHT.

05:48.580 --> 05:49.512
SO WHAT?
GIVE ME BACK THE PHONE.

05:49.620 --> 05:50.757
WHAT?
- THIS IS ROUGH.

05:50.860 --> 05:53.579
YOU'RE SCHEDULING SEX
WITH YOUR WIFE?

05:53.690 --> 05:55.863
- YEAH. LOOK, WE HAVE PLENTY
OF UNSCHEDULED SEX, OKAY?

05:55.970 --> 05:57.517
ONCE IN A WHILE,
WE HAVE DRY SPELLS,

05:57.630 --> 05:59.143
AND WE RELY ON GOING
TO FUNKYTOWN,

05:59.250 --> 06:00.410
AND YOU WILL TO, MY FRIEND.

06:00.530 --> 06:01.838
- NAH, I DON'T THINK SO.

06:01.940 --> 06:03.669
WE HAD IMPROMPTU SEX
ON THE KITCHEN FLOOR LAST NIGHT.

06:03.770 --> 06:05.180
AND LET ME TELL YOU,
WE DID NOT HAVE TO SCHEDULE IT.

06:05.290 --> 06:05.904
- NIECE.
NIECE IS IN THE ROOM.

06:06.020 --> 06:07.282
- LIBIDOS TOOK OVER.

06:07.400 --> 06:08.731
- NIECE.
- LIBIDOS.

06:08.850 --> 06:10.989
- NIECE, 11:00.
- WHEW.

06:11.090 --> 06:13.888
[playing Funkytown]

06:13.990 --> 06:15.571
- VERY FUNNY.

06:15.680 --> 06:17.090
- IS THAT FUNKYTOWN?

06:17.200 --> 06:18.337
I LOVE THAT SONG.

06:18.440 --> 06:21.955
WON'T YOU TAKE ME
TO FUNKYTOWN?

06:22.070 --> 06:23.059
IT'S A GOOD SONG.
- THANK YOU SO MUCH.

06:23.170 --> 06:25.058
- YOU'RE WELCOME.
- THANK YOU.

06:25.170 --> 06:26.239
- THAT WAS GOOD.
- HA.

06:26.350 --> 06:29.820
[Lucy Schwartz's
When We Were Young]

06:31.800 --> 06:34.451
WHEN WE WERE YOUNG
WE WERE SMALL

06:34.560 --> 06:38.075
BUT WE DIDN'T
KNOW IT

06:38.190 --> 06:41.705
AH AHH AH

06:41.810 --> 06:43.607
WHEN YOU WERE HURT
YOU WOULD SMILE

06:43.710 --> 06:48.056
SO YOU DIDN'T
SHOW IT

06:48.160 --> 06:51.709
AH AHH AH

06:51.820 --> 06:54.618
AND I

06:54.720 --> 06:59.407
CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'RE MINE

07:03.250 --> 07:05.866
CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE MINE

07:08.250 --> 07:10.901
CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE MINE

07:14.950 --> 07:15.905
- YEAH, SO MY MOM SAID
THAT I CAN USE HER CAR

07:16.020 --> 07:17.009
TWICE A WEEK, SO...

07:17.120 --> 07:18.280
- THAT'S AWESOME.

07:18.400 --> 07:18.809
- YEAH, IF YOU WANT,
WE CAN MAKE IT LIKE

07:18.920 --> 07:20.979
A REGULAR THING.

07:21.090 --> 07:24.218
YOU KNOW, THAT WAY
YOU DON'T HAVE TO TAKE THE BUS.

07:30.930 --> 07:34.229
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

07:34.350 --> 07:36.898
YOU'RE ALL QUIET.

07:38.520 --> 07:42.172
- DREW, WE NEED TO TALK.

07:42.280 --> 07:45.522
I, UM...

07:45.630 --> 07:47.211
I MET A GUY THIS SUMMER.

07:47.320 --> 07:52.565
AT CAMP.

07:52.670 --> 07:56.254
AND IT'S--
I MEAN, IT'S NOT LIKE--

07:56.370 --> 07:58.361
IT'S NOT SERIOUS OR...

07:58.470 --> 08:02.099
- WHAT, ARE YOU, LIKE, BREAKING
UP WITH ME OR SOMETHING?

08:04.650 --> 08:08.404
- PLEASE DON'T BE MAD.

08:08.520 --> 08:10.795
I REALLY CARE ABOUT YOU.

08:10.900 --> 08:12.652
AND, I MEAN, I STILL WANT
TO BE FRIENDS.

08:12.760 --> 08:16.389
- [scoffs]
- I'M SORRY.

08:16.490 --> 08:17.650
I WANTED TO TELL YOU SOONER,
BUT I JUST--

08:17.770 --> 08:20.455
I COULDN'T, AND THEN--
- YEAH, YOU DON'T WANT

08:20.560 --> 08:21.766
TO WALK IN THE FIRST DAY
OF SENIOR YEAR

08:21.880 --> 08:24.394
WITH ME ATTACHED TO YOU,
I GET IT.

08:24.500 --> 08:26.877
- DREW.

08:26.980 --> 08:30.529
- JUST--OHH.
YOU SHOULD JUST GO.

08:30.640 --> 08:32.608
THE--THE BELL'S GONNA RING.

08:32.710 --> 08:34.189
LIKE, YOU'RE GONNA BE LATE,
SO...

08:41.520 --> 08:45.513
[door shuts]

08:50.390 --> 08:52.312
[school bell rings]

08:54.810 --> 08:57.449
[battle sounds on TV]

08:57.570 --> 09:01.427
[cell phone jingles]

09:01.540 --> 09:04.179
- HEY.

09:04.300 --> 09:05.676
HOW IS HE?

09:05.780 --> 09:07.953
I'LL LET YOU ASK HIM YOURSELF.

09:08.060 --> 09:10.608
HEY...
YOUR MOM WANTS TO TALK TO YOU,

09:10.720 --> 09:13.166
IF YOU'RE UP TO IT.

09:13.270 --> 09:17.206
- HELLO?

09:17.310 --> 09:19.164
- YEAH, MY STOMACH STILL HURTS,

09:19.280 --> 09:23.558
BUT I THINK THE SOUP IS MAKING
IT A LITTLE BIT BETTER.

09:23.660 --> 09:27.312
YEAH, I THINK
IT WILL BE GOOD TOMORROW.

09:27.420 --> 09:32.323
[rock music]

09:32.430 --> 09:33.397
- THE GRAY?

09:33.500 --> 09:36.560
IT'S NICE, RIGHT?

09:36.670 --> 09:37.705
- IT'S NOT HORRIBLE, BUT...
- NO.

09:37.810 --> 09:39.675
IT'S NOT GOOD.
IT'S NOT GOOD.

09:39.780 --> 09:41.008
NO, I-I--
YOU'RE RIGHT.

09:41.130 --> 09:42.848
HOW ABOUT THIS, THOUGH?
I THOUGHT THAT WAS...

09:42.960 --> 09:45.599
OH, YEAH.
IT'S TOO TAN.

09:45.720 --> 09:48.029
NO, I DON'T LIKE IT EITHER.
OOH, DREW'S HERE.

09:48.130 --> 09:50.018
LISTEN, HE'S A NICE KID,
BUT HE'S VERY SHY.

09:50.140 --> 09:51.164
DON'T SCARE HIM.

09:51.280 --> 09:53.134
- WE HAVING A PLAYDATE NOW?

09:53.240 --> 09:54.684
- NO, IT WAS HIS FIRST DAY
OF SENIOR YEAR,

09:54.800 --> 09:55.824
SO YOU MIGHT LIKE
TO ASK HIM A QUESTION.

09:55.940 --> 09:58.693
- NO.
NO, I DON'T.

09:58.800 --> 10:00.688
- HI. HOW WAS IT?

10:00.800 --> 10:01.721
- IT WAS FINE.
- IT WAS OKAY?

10:01.840 --> 10:03.148
YOU DIDN'T CNOSH THE CAR?

10:03.250 --> 10:07.254
- DREW, YOU REMEMBER HANK
FROM THE FAMILY PORTRAIT.

10:07.360 --> 10:10.352
HANK, THIS IS MY SON DREW, WHO
YOU'VE BEEN WANTING TO TALK TO.

10:10.470 --> 10:14.634
HUH?

