AN ANSWER.

18:56.850 --> 18:57.919
- KIM?
- YEAH.

18:58.030 --> 18:59.236
ARLO'S MOM.

18:59.340 --> 19:00.375
- FRIDAY NIGHT'S ROUGH.

19:00.480 --> 19:01.549
I DON'T WANT TO BE
IN THE SESSION

19:01.650 --> 19:02.890
JUST STARING AT MY WATCH
THE WHOLE TIME.

19:03.000 --> 19:04.513
YOU KNOW, THE MUSICIANS
CAN KIND OF SENSE THAT.

19:04.620 --> 19:06.133
- COME ON.
IT'LL BE FUN.

19:06.240 --> 19:08.299
- WELL...
- WE NEED COUPLE FRIENDS.

19:08.420 --> 19:10.388
- ARE YOU SURE THAT'S A NEED
AND NOT A WANT?

19:10.490 --> 19:12.105
- YES.
- OKAY, LOOK,

19:12.220 --> 19:13.551
I CAN'T COMMIT
TO FRIDAY.

19:13.660 --> 19:15.901
MAYBE--I WON'T KNOW UNTIL I SEE
HOW THE SESSION'S GOING.

19:16.010 --> 19:18.217
CAN YOU MAYBE CHECK IN WITH THEM
ON FRIDAY AND TELL THEM?

19:18.320 --> 19:20.424
GIVE 'EM LIKE 80%?

19:20.530 --> 19:23.112
- ALL RIGHT.
- OKAY, THANKS.

19:23.230 --> 19:25.152
OH, HEY,
DO YOU WANT TO HOP IN?

19:25.260 --> 19:26.249
- NO, YOUR SISTER'S COMING

19:26.370 --> 19:27.462
IN, LIKE, 15 MINUTES
TO BRING JABBAR.

19:27.580 --> 19:29.536
- 15 MINUTES?
- YEAH.

19:29.650 --> 19:31.606
- WE CAN MAKE TWINS
IN 15 MINUTES, HONEY.

19:31.720 --> 19:33.676
COME ON.
- THAT DOESN'T TURN ME ON.

19:33.790 --> 19:35.121
- OH, ALL RIGHT.

19:35.240 --> 19:36.571
WELL, NICE CHATTING
WITH YOU.

19:36.690 --> 19:38.965
- YOU'RE GETTING WATER
EVERYWHERE.

19:39.070 --> 19:40.446
- I'M GONNA BE IN HERE.
- YEAH.

19:40.550 --> 19:42.552
- I WAS SERIOUS, OKAY?
AND THE IDEA OF AN INTERVIEW

19:42.660 --> 19:43.558
ABOUT A DOG
IS RIDICULOUS.

19:43.660 --> 19:44.558
- IT'S NOT.
- YOU KNOW WHY?

19:44.660 --> 19:47.220
- WHY?
- BECAUSE IT'S A DOG.

19:47.320 --> 19:49.459
IT'S NOT LIKE
WE'RE ADOPTING A BABY.

19:49.560 --> 19:51.619
RIGHT?
AND WE MADE AN AGREEMENT.

19:51.740 --> 19:53.731
WE AGREED THAT WE'D TAKE
OUR TIME WITH THIS.

19:53.840 --> 19:56.946
- YOU TOLD ME WHAT TO DO.
- IT'S THE FIRST DOG WE'VE SEEN.

19:57.050 --> 19:59.564
- HONEY, YOU TOLD ME--
- YES, AND THEN YOU TOLD MAX,

19:59.680 --> 20:02.228
WHICH COMPLETELY UNDERMINES US
MAKING THE DECISION ON OUR OWN.

20:02.330 --> 20:03.467
THAT'S WHAT HAPPENED.
- OKAY. FINE.

20:03.580 --> 20:05.719
YOU KNOW WHAT,
POINT TAKEN.

20:05.820 --> 20:06.980
YOU'RE RIGHT ABOUT THAT.
- THANK YOU.

20:07.100 --> 20:08.579
- YOU'RE ABSOLUTELY RIGHT.
I DID.

20:08.690 --> 20:10.408
BUT YOU SABOTAGED THE INTERVIEW
ON PURPOSE.

20:10.510 --> 20:11.829
- I DIDN'T SABOTAGE ANYTHING.
- YOU WENT IN THERE,

20:11.930 --> 20:13.750
AND YOU ACTED LIKE YOU WERE
ON BOARD, AND YOU WEREN'T.

20:13.860 --> 20:15.373
OKAY?
YOU SAID THAT YOU WANTED A DOG--

20:15.490 --> 20:16.275
- I WAS ON BOARD
WHEN WE FIRST GOT THERE.

20:16.380 --> 20:17.347
- YOU WASTED EVERYBODY'S TIME.

20:17.450 --> 20:18.792
- AND THEN THE DOGGY GESTAPO

20:18.900 --> 20:20.242
STARTED ASKING ME QUESTIONS

20:20.350 --> 20:21.556
ABOUT WHAT KIND
OF A DOG OWNER I'D BE.

20:21.660 --> 20:23.036
- YOU BROKE YOUR SON'S HEART.

20:23.150 --> 20:24.003
YOU BROKE
YOUR SON'S HEART.

20:24.110 --> 20:25.213
- I DID?
- YOU KNOW, YOU DID.

20:25.320 --> 20:26.799
HE LOVED THAT DOG.

20:26.910 --> 20:28.354
DID YOU SEE THE WAY IT WAS,
LIKE, SNUGGLING AND NUGGLING?

20:28.460 --> 20:29.188
- COME ON, HONEY,
IT'S $1,200 FOR THAT DOG.

20:29.290 --> 20:31.394
$1,200.
- SO WHAT?

20:31.500 --> 20:32.637
- I KNOW YOU LIKED THAT DOG.

20:32.740 --> 20:34.116
THERE ARE OTHER DOGS
OUT THERE.

20:34.230 --> 20:35.458
- IT'S A LOT OF MONEY,
BUT IT'S WORTH IT.

20:35.570 --> 20:37.049
OKAY?
I'LL DO ANYTHING...

20:37.160 --> 20:38.297
- ALL RIGHT.
- WITHIN REASON

20:38.400 --> 20:39.810
THAT YOU ASK
TO GET THAT DOG.

20:39.920 --> 20:41.740
- YOU WANT THAT DOG, FINE,
WE'LL GET THAT DOG.

20:41.860 --> 20:42.303
- YAY!
- BUT YOU SAID

20:42.410 --> 20:44.503
I'D GET ANYTHING I WANT?

20:44.620 --> 20:46.201
- YOU--ANYTHING.
I MEAN, DO YOU WANT MEATBALLS?

20:46.310 --> 20:48.062
I'LL MAKE YOU PASTA.

20:48.170 --> 20:50.513
FAGIOLI.
- HEY, KRISTINA.

20:50.620 --> 20:52.929
ANYTHING?

20:53.040 --> 20:54.484
- ANYTHING.
- ANYTHING?

20:54.590 --> 20:56.387
- LIKE FUNKYTOWN?
- YEAH.

20:56.490 --> 20:58.867
ANYTHING I WANT.
- OKAY.

20:58.980 --> 21:00.971
EXCEPT--YEAH, I WILL DO
FUNKYTOWN, BUT I'M NOT GONNA DO

21:01.080 --> 21:03.560
THAT ONE THING THAT YOU LIKE
TO DO, 'CAUSE IT HURTS.

21:03.670 --> 21:04.637
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
YOU SAID ANYTHING.

21:04.740 --> 21:06.879
- HOLD ON, HOLD ON.
- IS THAT HADDIE?

21:06.980 --> 21:08.220
- HELLO.

21:08.330 --> 21:09.467
- IT'S THE LADY.
- OH.

21:09.570 --> 21:10.810
- YES, THIS IS KRISTINA.

21:10.920 --> 21:12.467
- TELL HER $900.
- NO.

21:12.580 --> 21:15.504
- HI. YES, OF COURSE.
THANK YOU.

21:17.750 --> 21:19.684
OKAY.

21:19.790 --> 21:24.989
I UNDERSTAND.
THANK YOU FOR CALLING.

21:25.110 --> 21:28.762
THEY SOLD THE DOG.

21:28.870 --> 21:30.201
[thud]

21:30.320 --> 21:33.835
- SO...FUNKYTOWN?
- SO...

21:33.940 --> 21:34.804
NO?

21:39.640 --> 21:41.915
- HEY, GUYS, WAKE UP.
WAKE UP.

21:42.020 --> 21:42.327
- MAX, STOP.

21:42.430 --> 21:43.226
- WAKE UP.

21:43.330 --> 21:45.321
COME ON.
WAKE UP.

21:45.440 --> 21:47.431
- MAX, WE'RE ASLEEP!

21:47.540 --> 21:49.508
- I MADE A LIST
OF ALL THE REASONS

21:49.610 --> 21:50.986
WHY WE NEED THAT DOG.
ALL RIGHT?

21:51.100 --> 21:52.374
- HONEY.
- NUMBER ONE:

21:52.480 --> 21:54.539
DOGS, THEY'RE FUN.
THEY JUST ARE.

21:54.650 --> 21:58.609
NUMBER TWO:
DOGS TEACH RESPONSIBILITY.

21:58.730 --> 22:00.277
REASON NUMBER THREE:
THE DOG HAS BEEN SCREENED

22:00.380 --> 22:01.722
AND CERTIFIED.
NOW I DON'T KNOW

22:01.830 --> 22:02.899
WHY THAT'S SO AMAZING.
- THEY SOLD THE DOG.

22:03.010 --> 22:05.649
- THE WEB SITE MADE IT OUT
TO BE GOOD.

22:05.770 --> 22:06.452
- WHAT?

22:06.560 --> 22:09.381
- BABE, THEY SOLD THE DOG.

22:09.500 --> 22:10.489
I TALKED TO THE LADY
LAST NIGHT.

22:10.600 --> 22:12.636
I TALKED TO THE--
LISTEN--LISTEN TO ME.

22:12.740 --> 22:14.879
DON'T GET UPSET.
- NO, YOU GUYS SAID

22:14.980 --> 22:16.186
YOU WOULD SLEEP ON IT,
AND YOU SLEPT ON IT.

22:16.300 --> 22:17.528
- I KNEW THIS WAS GONNA HAPPEN,
HONEY.

22:17.640 --> 22:19.562
- AND NOW I WANT THAT DOG!
- MAX, TAKE IT EASY.

22:19.680 --> 22:20.840
I UNDERSTAND
YOU WANT THE DOG.

22:20.960 --> 22:22.359
THIS IS ONE OF THOSE THINGS
IN LIFE

22:22.470 --> 22:23.289
YOU'RE JUST GONNA HAVE
TO DEAL WITH, MAX.

22:23.410 --> 22:24.854
HONEY, I GOT
TO TAKE A SHOWER.

22:24.960 --> 22:25.540
- SOMEBODY ELSE
HAD A HOLD ON IT, OKAY?

22:25.650 --> 22:27.436
AND THEY CALLED FIRST.

22:27.550 --> 22:28.824
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?
- NO. NO.

22:28.930 --> 22:30.204
- ARE YOU KIDDING ME?
- I HAVE TO TAKE A SHOWER.

22:30.310 --> 22:31.516
- THIS IS UNFAIR!
- I CAN'T BELIEVE

22:31.620 --> 22:32.757
YOU'RE LEAVING ME RIGHT NOW.
- EVERYBODY, CHILL--

22:32.860 --> 22:34.179
IT'S ON THE CALENDAR.
YOU CAN CHECK IT OUT.

22:34.280 --> 22:35.895
I KNEW
THIS WAS GONNA HAPPEN.

22:36.000 --> 22:37.581
- ADAM.
- IT ISN'T FAIR!

22:37.700 --> 22:38.769
- OH, MY GOD.
- DAD, YOU SAID.

22:38.870 --> 22:40.519
- ADAM, ARE YOU KIDDING ME
RIGHT NOW?

22:40.630 --> 22:42.006
PLEASE COME BACK HERE.
WE'RE STILL DISCUSSING THIS.

22:42.110 --> 22:44.078
- I HAVE TO TAKE A SHOWER.
I SHOULD HAVE JUST SAID NO

22:44.190 --> 22:45.521
IN THE FIRST PLACE.
- THERE WILL BE OTHER DOGS.

22:45.640 --> 22:47.039
I PROMISE YOU THAT,
AND I WILL MAKE SURE

22:47.150 --> 22:48.469
THAT YOU GET--
- NO, WE NEED TO GET THAT DOG.

22:48.570 --> 22:49.946
- SWEETIE.
- WE NEED TO GET THAT DOG.

22:50.050 --> 22:51.426
- THE DOG IS TAKEN.
- NO, WE'RE GOING RIGHT NOW...

22:51.540 --> 22:52.529
- CALM DOWN.
ADAM!

22:52.640 --> 22:54.119
- TO TELL THEM
THEY MADE A MISTAKE.

22:54.230 --> 22:55.436
- REALLY?
REALLY?

22:55.540 --> 22:56.746
- WHEN I WAS YOUR AGE,

22:56.850 --> 22:59.159
MY PARENTS MADE ME GO
TO SWIM TEAM.

22:59.270 --> 23:00.612
OOH, I HATED IT.

23:00.720 --> 23:02.881
I HAD TO GET UP AT 6:00 A.M.
EVERY MORNING.

23:03.000 --> 23:04.820
BUT THEY MADE ME GO,
AND I'M GLAD THAT I DID,

23:04.930 --> 23:07.967
BECAUSE NOW I'M
A REALLY GOOD SWIMMER.

23:08.070 --> 23:10.584
RIGHT, SYD?
- YUP. REMEMBER THAT ONE TIME

23:10.690 --> 23:12.339
YOU CAME TO MY SWIM CLASS
AND YOU ALMOST DROWNDED ME?

23:12.460 --> 23:15.031
- YES, I REMEMBER THAT,

23:15.150 --> 23:16.663
BUT YOU DIDN'T DROWN, 'CAUSE
YOU WERE SUCH A STRONG SWIMMER.

23:16.770 --> 23:19.182
THAT WAS GREAT.
YOU LEARNED.

23:19.290 --> 23:20.427
OKAY, LET'S GO, GUYS.

23:20.530 --> 23:21.736
- LET'S GO.

23:24.610 --> 23:27.295
- COME ON.
AREN'T YOU COMING?

23:27.400 --> 23:28.150
- IT'S OKAY.
YOU CAN WALK IN WITH SYDNEY.

23:28.260 --> 23:30.262
- COME ON.

23:30.370 --> 23:32.747
- LET'S GO.

23:33.270 --> 23:35.955
- OKAY.

23:36.060 --> 23:39.063
[car horns honking]

23:39.170 --> 23:41.343
VICTOR, YOU HAVE
TO GO TO SCHOOL.

23:41.450 --> 23:43.372
YOU CAN'T MISS THREE DAYS
IN A ROW.

23:43.490 --> 23:44.479
- MY STOMACH
STILL HURTS.

23:44.590 --> 23:47.457
[car horns honking]

23:50.250 --> 23:52.525
SYDNEY, GO IN.
OKAY, SWEETIE?

23:52.630 --> 23:53.904
- OKAY.
- OKAY.

23:57.050 --> 24:01.009
VICTOR, I KNOW
A NEW SCHOOL CAN BE SCARY.

24:02.640 --> 24:08.294
AND I KNOW THAT IT MIGHT
STILL BE SCARY LIVING WITH US.

24:08.410 --> 24:10.503
BUT I NEED YOU
TO BE BRAVE FOR ME, OKAY?

24:10.620 --> 24:14.966
I NEED YOU TO DO THIS.

24:21.250 --> 24:22.831
HONEY.

24:22.940 --> 24:26.524
OKAY, I WILL STAY
RIGHT HERE.

24:26.630 --> 24:28.871
YOU GO TO SCHOOL,

24:28.980 --> 24:30.629
BUT, IF YOU NEED ME,
IF YOU NEED ANYTHING,

24:30.740 --> 24:32.560
I'LL BE RIGHT HERE.

24:32.670 --> 24:34.979
- ALL DAY?
- ALL DAY.

24:38.090 --> 24:40.229
- YOU SWEAR?
- DO YOU KNOW PINKY SWEAR?

24:45.620 --> 24:48.259
- UGH, WELL, THAT JUST MAKES ME
HATE HER.

24:48.380 --> 24:49.779
I MEAN, YOU KNOW,
I DON'T HATE HER.

24:49.900 --> 24:50.400
SHE'S A VERY NICE GIRL,
BUT, I MEAN,

24:50.520 --> 24:52.863
I JUST HATE HER.

24:52.970 --> 24:53.789
THAT'S HORRIBLE.

24:53.900 --> 24:55.242
HE JUST SAT ALL BY HIMSELF?

24:55.350 --> 24:58.217
OH, MY GOD, WELL, I GUESS,
WHAT IS SHE SUPPOSED TO DO?

24:58.320 --> 25:01.175
YOU KNOW, I MEAN,
WHAT DOES HE HAVE NOW, CALCULUS?

25:01.290 --> 25:02.769
OKAY.
ALL RIGHT.

25:02.880 --> 25:04.666
KEEP AN EYE OUT.
CALL ME IN AN HOUR.

25:04.770 --> 25:06.397
OKAY.
LOVE YOU TOO.

25:06.500 --> 25:08.775
BYE.
OH, MY GOD.

25:08.880 --> 25:10.745
HORRIBLE.
DREW'S HAVING A MISERABLE DAY.

25:10.850 --> 25:12.704
- MM-HMM.
- THANK GOD

25:12.820 --> 25:14.913
MY FIANCE IS THERE, YOU KNOW,
TO KEEP AN EYE OUT FOR HIM.

25:15.030 --> 25:17.919
- YEAH, THAT'S NOT WEIRD
AT ALL.

25:18.030 --> 25:19.167
- IT'S NOT WEIRD.
WHY IS IT WEIRD?

25:19.270 --> 25:22.068
- IT'S ODD.
- WHY?

25:22.170 --> 25:23.512
- WHATEVER. THAT'S ALL RIGHT.
LET'S GO.

25:23.620 --> 25:25.099
- NO, NO, PLEASE,
WHAT'S WEIRD ABOUT IT?

25:25.210 --> 25:26.928
I'D LIKE YOUR OPINION.
CAN YOU JUST TELL ME?

25:27.040 --> 25:29.588
- BOY, OH, BOY.
- LOOK, I WOULD LOVE

25:29.700 --> 25:31.099
A MAN'S OPINION.

25:31.210 --> 25:33.485
- THERE'S A GUY WHO WORKED
FOR ME FOR TWO YEARS.

25:33.600 --> 25:35.101
HE NEVER SAID ANYTHING.

25:35.220 --> 25:37.359
I DIDN'T KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT HIS PERSONAL LIFE.

25:37.460 --> 25:39.041
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
HE WAS MARRIED.

25:39.150 --> 25:40.287
I MISS THAT GUY.

25:40.400 --> 25:43.779
- WELL, I'M NOT THAT GUY.

25:43.880 --> 25:45.632
- BERNIE.

25:45.750 --> 25:46.842
- I'M SORRY
I'M NOT BERNIE,

25:46.950 --> 25:48.394
BUT CAN'T YOU JUST TELL ME
YOUR OPINION?

25:48.510 --> 25:52.025
- YOU WANT TO KNOW MY OPINION?
I THINK YOU'RE BEING AN IDIOT.

25:52.130 --> 25:53.711
- WOW. OKAY.

25:53.820 --> 25:54.684
THAT'S CONSTRUCT IVE.

25:54.790 --> 25:57.611
- NO, YOU ARE.
- OKAY. WHY?

25:57.720 --> 25:59.608
- YOUR SON GOT DUMPED,
AND YOU'RE ALL OVER HIM.

25:59.730 --> 26:01.584
YOU'RE FAWNING OVER HIM.

26:01.690 --> 26:03.100
- I CARE. I'M INTERESTED.

26:03.210 --> 26:04.108
- "OH, IT'LL BE OKAY.
DOODLEPUSS, DON'T WORRY."

26:04.210 --> 26:05.689
- I'M NOT GONNA CALL HIM
DOODLEPUSS.

26:05.800 --> 26:07.006
I'M WORRIED,
AND HE'S IN PAIN.

26:07.110 --> 26:08.486
I'M HIS MOTHER.
- OF COURSE HE'S IN PAIN.

26:08.600 --> 26:09.624
OF COURSE.
WOMEN--

26:09.740 --> 26:12.561
WOMEN ARE CONNIVING
SOUL-CRUSHERS,

26:12.670 --> 26:14.809
AND, IF HE REALIZES THAT,
HE'LL BE OKAY.

26:14.910 --> 26:17.117
HE HAS A CHANCE.
- OH, MY GOD.

26:17.230 --> 26:18.219
SOMEBODY DID NOT
GET INVITED TO PROM.

26:18.330 --> 26:19.979
- I DID GET INVITED
TO PROM.

26:20.090 --> 26:21.432
THAT'S RIGHT.
I WAS PROM KING.

26:21.540 --> 26:23.269
- NO, YOU WEREN'T.
- I WAS PROM KING,

26:23.370 --> 26:24.507
I GOT LAID,
THE WHOLE DEAL.

26:24.610 --> 26:25.713
- WOW.
- ALL RIGHT. YOU KNOW WHY?

26:25.820 --> 26:27.094
'CAUSE I WAS COOL.
I DROVE A HONDA CX500.

26:27.200 --> 26:30.021
I LISTENED TO THE DEAD
INSTEAD OF DISCO.

26:30.140 --> 26:33.166
I SOLD POT OUT OF THE BACK
OF JOEY NICHOLS' CAR,

26:33.280 --> 26:34.304
AND WE MADE A LOT OF MONEY,

26:34.420 --> 26:35.921
AND MY MOTHER NEVER EVEN MET
MY GIRLFRIENDS,

26:36.040 --> 26:39.248
MUCH LESS GAVE ME
DATING ADVICE.

26:39.350 --> 26:40.658
I WOULD HAVE LAUGHED AT HER.

26:40.770 --> 26:44.592
- SO I SHOULD TELL DREW
TO, WAIT, GET A MOTORCYCLE

26:44.700 --> 26:47.112
AND SELL POT, AND THAT'LL
MAKE HIM FEEL BETTER?

26:47.220 --> 26:49.393
- NO, IT'S SIMPLER THAN THAT.
- WELL, WHAT SHOULD HE DO?

26:49.500 --> 26:50.592
- YOU KNOW WHAT HE SHOULD DO?

26:50.710 --> 26:51.802
HE SHOULD SLEEP
WITH HER BEST FRIEND.

26:51.920 --> 26:53.114
'CAUSE THAT
SHE'LL TAKE NOTICE OF.

26:53.230 --> 26:54.561
- [gasp5]

26:54.680 --> 26:55.817
- 'CAUSE SHE'S GONNA
DO IT TO HIM.

26:55.920 --> 26:57.501
THAT'S JUST THE THING.
SHE'S GONNA DO IT TO HIM.

26:57.610 --> 26:58.508
SO GET THERE FIRST--

26:58.610 --> 27:00.293
AND YOU SEE?

27:00.410 --> 27:02.401
SEE, YOU ASKED MY OPINION,

27:02.510 --> 27:03.613
AND THEN THIS HAPPENS.

27:03.720 --> 27:04.687
AND THAT DIDN'T HAPPEN
WITH BERNIE.

27:04.790 --> 27:06.997
WHY DID YOU ASK ME, THOUGH?

27:07.100 --> 27:09.375
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

27:09.480 --> 27:13.587
- I...

27:13.700 --> 27:18.103
AM GONNA GO GET
SOME COFFEE.

27:19.630 --> 27:21.257
[door opens]

27:21.360 --> 27:24.249
[door shuts]

27:38.650 --> 27:41.369
[school bell rings]

27:46.660 --> 27:49.003
[kids chattering]

28:09.650 --> 28:10.787
- HEY, BEAUTY.

28:10.890 --> 28:11.959
- HEY.
WHERE'S JABBAR?

28:12.060 --> 28:14.096
- I DON'T KNOW.
I JUST GOT HERE.

28:14.200 --> 28:16.088
JABBAR?
- WAIT, YOU DIDN'T GET HIM?

28:16.210 --> 28:18.587
- WHAT, NO,
YOU WERE GONNA GET HIM?

28:18.690 --> 28:20.100
- YOU WERE SUPPOSED TO GET HIM.
I TOLD YOU I HAD A CLASS.

28:20.210 --> 28:22.132
- NO, NO, NO,
YOU DIDN'T TELL ME THAT.

28:22.250 --> 28:24.969
- YES, I DID.
YOU SAID YOU HAD IT COVERED.

28:25.080 --> 28:26.695
- OH, MY GOSH, YOU'RE RIGHT.
I DID.

28:26.800 --> 28:29.075
I'M SO SORRY.
UM, I SHOULD HAVE--

28:29.190 --> 28:29.622
- WHAT?
PUT IT IN A FREAKIN' CALENDAR?

28:29.740 --> 28:32.254
WHAT A NOTION.

28:32.360 --> 28:34.464
- WHOA, HEY, HEY.
STOP SIGN, STOP SIGN.

28:34.570 --> 28:37.050
- YOU KNOW WHAT? I KNOW YOU
THINK IT'S SO UNCOOL

28:37.160 --> 28:38.741
AND EVERYTHING TO HAVE
A SCHEDULE, BUT, GUESS WHAT?

28:38.850 --> 28:40.260
THAT'S WHAT PEOPLE DO.
THEY ORGANIZE THEIR LIVES

28:40.370 --> 28:42.019
SO CRAP LIKES THIS
DOESN'T HAPPEN!

28:42.130 --> 28:44.269
- THE SCHOOL'S RIGHT HERE.
- I KNOW WHERE HIS SCHOOL IS!

28:44.370 --> 28:46.930
- OKAY, WELL, LISTEN,
YOU'RE FREAKING OUT,

28:47.030 --> 28:48.258
AND HE'S JUST SITTING IN SCHOOL.
IT'S NOT A BIG DEAL.

28:48.380 --> 28:50.757
- YOU LEI-T OUR CHILD IN SCHOOL.
THAT'S A BIG DEAL.

28:50.860 --> 28:52.088
- I THINK YOU'RE OVERREACTING
JUST A LITTLE BIT.

28:52.210 --> 28:53.234
- DON'T TELL ME
I'M OVERREACTING.

28:53.350 --> 28:55.033
- YOU'RE BLOWING
THROUGH STOP SIGNS.

28:55.140 --> 28:56.129
- YOU KNOW WHAT?
- YOU'RE LOCKING UP THE BRAKES

28:56.250 --> 28:57.274
